<item>
            <title>[FLINK-3369] RemoteTransportException should be instance of CancelTaskException</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-3369</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;RemoteTransportException&lt;/tt&gt; is thrown when a consuming task is notified about failure at the producer side. This should not be reported as the root cause of the job failure. By making it an instance of &lt;tt&gt;CancelTaskException&lt;/tt&gt; it will not be reported as a failure, but as a cancellation.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12937537">FLINK-3369</key>
            <summary>RemoteTransportException should be instance of CancelTaskException</summary>
